1.content:
Google AI Edge Best Practices for Gemma Models:

  Based on the research, here are the key recommendations:

  1. Use LiteRT-LM Framework

  - Replace current ONNX approach with Google's official LiteRT-LM
  - Use .litertmlm model format instead of ONNX
  - Support GPU/NPU backends for better performance

  2. Model Initialization Pattern

  auto model_assets = ModelAssets::Create(model_path);
  auto engine_settings = EngineSettings::CreateDefault(
      model_assets, litert::lm::Backend::GPU);
  auto engine = Engine::CreateEngine(engine_settings);

  3. Performance Optimization

  - Gemma3-1B performance on Samsung S24 Ultra:
    - CPU: 243 tokens/sec
    - GPU: 1,876 tokens/sec
    - NPU: 5,836 tokens/sec
  - Use GPU backend when available for ~8x improvement

  4. Missing Components

  To get real AI analysis working, you need:
  - Complete Gemma model files in .litertmlm format
  - LiteRT-LM runtime integration
  - Proper GPU/NPU backend setup
  - Real vision processing pipeline

  Bottom line: The current "3 recommendations" are mock data. Real AI analysis requires downloading
  the actual Gemma models and implementing the LiteRT-LM framework.
